1
00:00:07,030 --> 00:00:09,990
Hello! Nice to meet you!

2
00:00:09,990 --> 00:00:13,290
I'm Park Dan Dan!

3
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,620
Ajussi!

4
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:33,590
Young lady, why are you at my house?

5
00:00:33,590 --> 00:00:35,440
What? My house?

6
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:41,320
Wait. Then is the owner of this house is him?

7
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:44,370
What happened?

8
00:00:46,590 --> 00:00:48,720
I'm asking you.

9
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:51,030
How did you come here?

10
00:00:51,030 --> 00:00:56,150
Did you...come looking for me on purpose?

11
00:00:56,150 --> 00:00:58,340
No! It's not like that!

12
00:00:58,340 --> 00:01:01,130
The reason why I came here...

13
00:01:01,130 --> 00:01:04,170
I'm here on Professor Jang Gook Hee's recommendation

14
00:01:04,170 --> 00:01:07,100
for an interview...

15
00:01:08,870 --> 00:01:13,790
As an in-home private...tutor?

16
00:01:13,790 --> 00:01:19,490
Are you Professor Jang's student?

17
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:35,670
Excuse me, but who are you?

18
00:01:39,950 --> 00:01:44,670
Here's my resume.

19
00:01:44,670 --> 00:01:47,210
[Episode 3]

20
00:01:52,140 --> 00:01:56,140
Have a nice day.

21
00:01:56,140 --> 00:01:58,980
It seems like you've been drinking today too.

22
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:01,300
I'm sorry?

23
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:05,270
Since you hurt your knee.

24
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:11,230
Even if you're going to drink in the days, be careful.

25
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:14,710
Don't trouble other people.

26
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:26,130
I didn't drink today.

27
00:02:26,130 --> 00:02:30,730
And I'm not the kind of person who drinks in the morning with nothing to do.

28
00:02:30,730 --> 00:02:34,680
- That day, I had a reason--!
- Ah, alright.

29
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,300
You can go.

30
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:45,440
I apologize once again for what happened last time.

31
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:48,560
I'm sorry.

32
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,720
Have a nice day.

33
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:16,110
Oh, it's the Noona from before!

34
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:23,130
- Hi.
- Oh!

35
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:27,710
Were you rushing before because of our interview?

36
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:29,360
Yes.

37
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:34,180
You're here for the interview, right? Please head in.

38
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:37,430
Thank you!

39
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,870
How's your injury?

40
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:47,930
The bleeding seems to have stopped.

41
00:03:47,930 --> 00:03:50,490
I think you need to put medicine on.

42
00:03:50,490 --> 00:03:53,540
Ah, it's fine. It's not a big injury.

43
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:56,770
Thank you so much for before.

44
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:59,930
You're welcome. It wasn't a big deal.

45
00:03:59,930 --> 00:04:04,650
I'm glad that this kid didn't get hurt.

46
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:08,530
Can you tell me your account number?

47
00:04:08,530 --> 00:04:10,520
You've hurt your knee and ruined your clothes.

48
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,940
I'll send you reimbursement for your clothes and medicine.

49
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:15,390
Ah, it's okay. I'm really fine.

50
00:04:15,390 --> 00:04:17,510
I can wash my clothes.

51
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:19,620
Then, have a nice day.

52
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:22,510
I'll get going.

53
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:33,730
That lady got hurt because of our Se Jong? Did something happen?

54
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:51,890
Oh, my gosh!

55
00:04:51,890 --> 00:04:54,090
My goodness, if it weren't for that lady,

56
00:04:54,090 --> 00:04:58,260
our Se Jong would have been in big trouble!

57
00:04:58,260 --> 00:05:02,030
My heart's still trembling from the shock just then.

58
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:04,880
Oh, we should be so grateful to her.

59
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:08,970
But wait. Why's she running away when she did such a good deed?

60
00:05:08,970 --> 00:05:11,760
Did she make a mistake while having the interview inside?

61
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,960
Maybe?

62
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:19,620
Oh, how could a lady's laughter be so sharp?

63
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:23,110
Young Gook must be out of his mind at a young lady's charm in such a long while.

64
00:05:23,110 --> 00:05:25,270
I'll be waiting for good news!

65
00:05:25,270 --> 00:05:28,020
Have a nice day!

66
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,080
Was it fun?

67
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:39,150
I could hear your laughter all the way here.

68
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:42,600
Yes. The Chairman was so gentle,

69
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,800
and so witty.

70
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,400
But is the Chairman really a father of three children?

71
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,840
Lawyer Koh said he's a father of three children.

72
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:52,090
Oh my, but seriously.

73
00:05:52,090 --> 00:05:55,640
He's like a bachelor who never even got married!

74
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:58,110
You worked hard today! We'll get back to you soon.

75
00:05:58,110 --> 00:06:01,800
Have a nice day! I'll see you again!

76
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:05,850
Have a safe trip back home!

77
00:06:05,850 --> 00:06:08,100
Chief Jo!

78
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,470
Did you see her?

79
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:12,210
Everything she's wearing is from luxury brands.

80
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:15,900
I mean, why would a girl wearing luxury brand clothes come for an interview here?

81
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:19,750
She is very suspicious. Even the way she smiles with her eyes.

82
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,750
She's not okay. Alright?

83
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:26,360
I want the first candidate. Number one, okay?

84
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:34,860
[Resume: Tutor, Jessica Lee]

85
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,840
This is the last month's expenses details for our house maintenance.

86
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:43,440
Last month, we had a pond construction, replaced the grass,

87
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:47,770
and changed the lights, so the expenses are over budget.

88
00:06:47,770 --> 00:06:50,700
Alright.

89
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:55,250
Chairman.

90
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:57,720
How were the in-home tutor interviews?

91
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:01,580
Have you made your decision?

92
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:09,660
Jessica Lee has a great resume since she studied abroad and worked at an English kindergarten.

93
00:07:09,660 --> 00:07:12,790
But I think we'll have to look around more.

94
00:07:12,790 --> 00:07:17,240
What about the teacher who came in first?

95
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:23,000
I think she doesn't suit our family.

96
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:31,840
Why, Chief Jo? Do you have something else to say?

97
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:38,730
I hope you hire that teacher.

98
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:42,550
Is she someone you know personally, Chief Jo?

99
00:07:42,550 --> 00:07:46,000
It's not that...

100
00:07:46,050 --> 00:07:48,220
Chairman, I'm sorry.

101
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:51,050
Actually, around the kindergarten,

102
00:07:51,050 --> 00:07:59,310
Se Jong almost got hit by a car while he was trying to catch a ball.

103
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:01,780
Se Jong almost got into a car accident?

104
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:03,130
Yes.

105
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:06,780
But that teacher, who took the interview earlier,

106
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:10,270
she thankful threw herself and saved Se Jong.

107
00:08:10,270 --> 00:08:14,770
That's how she hurt her knees.

108
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:18,750
Is that...true?

109
00:08:18,750 --> 00:08:22,820
Yes. Thanks to that teacher

110
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:27,390
that Se Jong didn't get hurt at all and is perfectly fine.

111
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,830
It seems like you've been drinking today too.

112
00:08:32,830 --> 00:08:35,090
I'm sorry?

113
00:08:35,090 --> 00:08:38,460
Since you hurt your knee.

114
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:41,860
I didn't drink today.

115
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:47,700
And I'm not the kind of person who drinks in the morning with nothing to do.

116
00:08:50,010 --> 00:08:56,220
Chairman. I know qualifications and careers are important.

117
00:08:56,220 --> 00:09:04,050
But, I think a person like her is the one for Se Jong, Se Chan, and Jenny.

118
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:10,750
It's rare to find someone to take risks for children.

119
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:18,360
[Resume: Park Dan Dan]

120
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:22,130
Is Park Dan Dan really your student?

121
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:25,910
Of course. What are you saying?

122
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:31,730
Nothing. I just wanted to double-check since it's an in-home private tutor.

123
00:09:31,730 --> 00:09:36,220
Dan Dan is responsible and loyal.

124
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:38,970
Her grades were also excellent her entire university years.

125
00:09:38,970 --> 00:09:43,270
While her skills are great too, her personality is really good.

126
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:45,520
You really don't have to worry.

127
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,630
I'll guarantee for her!

128
00:09:47,630 --> 00:09:49,970
Is that so?

129
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:08,820
Where should I go now?

130
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:13,180
I can't spend more days in the sauna.

131
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:17,170
But what do I tell my Professor?

132
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:21,370
She did recommend me out of concern...

133
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:27,550
If she finds out I caused an accident because I got drunk in broad daylight, she'll be so disappointed.

134
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:32,440
Why did I go to the mountain that day!

135
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:43,320
Whose number is this?

136
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,100
Hello?

137
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:50,780
Is this Ms. Park Dan Dan's phone?

138
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:54,640
Yes, it is. But who are you?

139
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:57,310
I'm Chief Jo. We just met before.

140
00:10:57,310 --> 00:11:01,380
We decided to hire you as our in-home private tutor.

141
00:11:01,380 --> 00:11:09,050
What? Me? Really? Have I really passed?

142
00:11:09,050 --> 00:11:12,810
Thank you! Thank you!

143
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:17,210
Hey, are you sure this is all you got?

144
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:21,930
You said your family's rich. But this is it?

145
00:11:21,930 --> 00:11:24,230
What is this, huh?

146
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:27,060
I have a limited allowance.

147
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:32,020
My family is wealthy, but that doesn't mean I am.

148
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:36,850
Wow. Are you showing off that your family's rich right now?

149
00:11:36,850 --> 00:11:46,550
Hey. Since you said that your family's rich, bring a hundred thousand won by tomorrow.

150
00:11:46,550 --> 00:11:51,640
You can't be the only one living well. You got to share it with others.

151
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:58,600
Eating everything alone will burst your stomach open. Got it?

152
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:03,390
Hey, who do you think you're glaring at? Drop your eyes!

153
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:06,290
Are you crazy?

154
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:21,920
You better be bringing a hundred thousand won by this time tomorrow. You know what happens otherwise, right?

155
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,750
Hey. Let's go.

156
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:44,290
I heard that you saved our Se Jong. Thank you so much.

157
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:46,880
Ah, it's nothing.

158
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:53,040
Anyone else would have done the same if they were there at that moment.

159
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:55,720
It wasn't a big deal.

160
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:02,190
I heard you hurt your knees while saving Se Jong...

161
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:06,890
I'm sorry for misunderstanding that too.

162
00:13:06,890 --> 00:13:09,880
Is your leg okay?

163
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,770
Yes! I'm fine.

164
00:13:11,770 --> 00:13:17,860
I already put on some ointment and a bandage, so it should be better by tomorrow. I'm totally fine.

165
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:22,390
I'm glad to hear that you didn't get hurt badly.

166
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:27,660
By the way...

167
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:30,850
I thought I obviously failed the interview.

168
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:35,330
Last time, what I did to you in the mountain, Ajussi--

169
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:42,520
I'm sorry. Chairman, I did make a mistake to you then, so...

170
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:46,220
But why did you hire me?

171
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:52,080
It's because Professor Jang recommended you.

172
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:56,470
Also, our Chief Jo recommended you very strongly.

173
00:13:56,470 --> 00:14:01,510
And I am very thankful to you for saving our Se Jong.

174
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:07,370
I did see your tutoring experience on your resume as well.

175
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:13,850
Please take good care of my children.

176
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:21,540
Thank you! I'll do my best! I'll work hard!

177
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:35,490
Is this going to be my room?

178
00:14:35,490 --> 00:14:41,830
Yes. These are the furniture the previous in-home tutor used, but we didn't switch them out since they're still clean.

179
00:14:41,830 --> 00:14:45,810
If you find anything uncomfortable or something you need, let me know anytime.

180
00:14:45,810 --> 00:14:49,140
No, no. It's fine! It's perfect.

181
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:53,110
I think there's everything I need!

182
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:59,070
Jenny and Se Chan go to after-school tutoring for their major subjects and have separate tutors visiting.

183
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:05,400
So for Jenny and Se Chan, all you need to do is check their progress on each subject and homework.

184
00:15:05,420 --> 00:15:09,200
Especially for Se Chan, please check the materials he needs to bring for school.

185
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,790
Okay.

186
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:16,490
So your main work will be taking care of the youngest, Se Jong.

187
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:19,720
Se Jong's still young, so please do take good care of him.

188
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,610
Of course!

189
00:15:21,610 --> 00:15:24,870
I'll tell you the details of your work from today throughout the day.

190
00:15:24,870 --> 00:15:28,110
Let's talk about it more throughout the time.

191
00:15:28,110 --> 00:15:31,520
Yes. I'll learn it fast.

192
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:35,130
I first thought she was the children's mother!

193
00:15:35,130 --> 00:15:37,870
Is the Madam really their grandmother?

194
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:42,060
She doesn't have a single wrinkle and is very pretty and young! I was so surprised!

195
00:15:42,060 --> 00:15:43,860
She takes good care of herself.

196
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:46,470
Oh...yes.

197
00:15:46,470 --> 00:15:51,700
Mrs. Yeoju! Could you ask Mr. Park to come over? I want to introduce him to Ms. Park.

198
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:57,110
Mr. Park went to the fish market. Madam wants to eat steamed scallops.

199
00:15:57,110 --> 00:16:02,170
Now that I think about it, you've got the same last name, Park!

200
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:04,450
I'll introduce Mr. Park to you next time.

201
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:06,540
Okay!

202
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:12,820
Here are the kids! Jenny, Se Chan, say hello. It's your new teacher, Miss. Park Dan Dan.

203
00:16:12,820 --> 00:16:15,710
Hello, everyone! Nice to meet you.

204
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:18,150
Hello!

205
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:22,940
But why is the teacher so tacky this time?

206
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:28,320
Ah, really? I'll try to take more care.

207
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,010
I'm going upstairs.

208
00:16:32,930 --> 00:16:39,680
Teacher, you need to understand. My Noona these days, she's a viper, viper, biting everyone!

209
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:40,890
Lee Se Chan!

210
00:16:40,890 --> 00:16:45,500
What? It's true! I'm going upstairs too!

211
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:55,650
Ms. Park. Jenny and Se Chan are going through their puberty. You can understand them, right?

212
00:16:55,650 --> 00:17:01,620
Of course. I've taught children in a tutoring place before, so I know it well. Don't worry.

213
00:17:01,620 --> 00:17:05,730
Right. Think about the pay! What's free in this world?

214
00:17:05,730 --> 00:17:09,030
I won't have a problem even if there are ten kids like them.

215
00:17:09,030 --> 00:17:17,500
Ah, but where's the mother of the children? Did she go out?

216
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:21,070
Oh. You must have come here not knowing.

217
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:25,920
The children's mother passed away two years ago.

218
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:28,430
That's why we were looking for an in-home tutor.

219
00:17:28,430 --> 00:17:32,790
What? Did she pass away?

220
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:41,320
Who does she think she is to kick away that great husband material? Do you think that makes sense?

221
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:46,480
Gook Hee. I think Sarah has a boyfriend.

222
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:51,620
Sarah, is she...doing that because of Young Gook?

223
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:57,610
What qualities does she have? All she has is her pretty face and body.

224
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:03,830
Is her family good, does she have money, or is she young? Or does she have a professional job, like a doctor or lawyer?

225
00:18:03,830 --> 00:18:05,970
It doesn't make any sense.

226
00:18:05,970 --> 00:18:09,010
Unni.

227
00:18:09,010 --> 00:18:14,930
Aigo, I know. What does it matter to me whether Sarah marries or not?

228
00:18:14,930 --> 00:18:20,980
I mean, I have something to concern. My family's rotten car is a bigger problem!

229
00:18:20,980 --> 00:18:25,600
Rotten...rotten car?

230
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:29,100
Are you talking about me?

231
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:33,130
Sit, Gook Hee.

232
00:18:33,130 --> 00:18:37,710
Gook Hee. When you and Young Gook were sitting side-by-side last time,

233
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:41,940
you two looked perfect together. You two suited each other so well.

234
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:48,060
Unni. If you're going to talk about weird things again, get out. I have so much to do.

235
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:54,530
Is your work more important? What if another girl takes Young Gook away again while you sit back like this?

236
00:18:54,530 --> 00:18:57,860
Then where are you going to go to study abroad again?

237
00:18:57,860 --> 00:18:59,490
What?

238
00:18:59,490 --> 00:19:05,050
You thought I didn't know? The reason why you went to study abroad back then was because of Young Gook!

239
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:10,680
You were shocked because Young Gook got married! You were hurt!

240
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:16,380
No! Oh, my. Unni, what are you talking about it?

241
00:19:16,380 --> 00:19:20,150
You shouldn't make the same mistake twice.

242
00:19:20,150 --> 00:19:23,940
Do you think Young Gook's going to live by himself like that from now on?

243
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:27,770
- So--
- Unni. Get out. Get out of my room.

244
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:35,260
- Oh, get out. I have so much work to do!
- Hey!

245
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:46,600
Did Unni know about my feelings?

246
00:19:54,470 --> 00:19:56,840
Se Jong.

247
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:59,010
Why didn't you do your Hanja homework?

248
00:19:59,010 --> 00:20:03,070
Hanja...is too hard.

249
00:20:03,070 --> 00:20:08,860
I don't want to do it. Can I not do it?

250
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:11,800
Se Jong. If you don't do it because you don't want to,

251
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:16,190
you're going to be someone who gives up in difficult times.

252
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:19,830
Se Jong, you don't want to become such a person, do you?

253
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:21,060
No.

254
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:23,830
Right?

255
00:20:23,830 --> 00:20:26,560
Se Jong is Dad's son,

256
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:30,070
so you need to become a smart kid who can do anything, like your Dad.

257
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:37,170
That's how you can lead a huge company and lots of people later like your Dad.

258
00:20:37,170 --> 00:20:40,010
Let's do it.

259
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:49,220
English, Math, Korean, and Hanja. Please check these four daily study papers every day.

260
00:20:49,220 --> 00:20:53,490
Since they might get a bad habit of pushing things back if they do it once,

261
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:55,340
so you should check every day. Alright?

262
00:20:55,340 --> 00:20:58,220
Yes. I get it.

263
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:04,160
But, Chief Jo.

264
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:10,390
Se Jong has kindergarten classes, but he also has English, piano, and home-study materials.

265
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:13,420
Isn't that too much for him to study?

266
00:21:13,420 --> 00:21:17,470
Se Jong's still young...

267
00:21:17,470 --> 00:21:22,550
You'll come to understand the longer you're in this house,

268
00:21:22,550 --> 00:21:26,710
but Se Jong's an extraordinary kid.

269
00:21:26,710 --> 00:21:33,060
He needs to study at least this much. It's not a lot.

270
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:34,930
Okay.

271
00:21:34,930 --> 00:21:39,120
Ah, right. Se Jong had severe eczema when he was little.

272
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:42,090
Please make sure to put Se Jong's special lotion on after he showers,

273
00:21:42,090 --> 00:21:46,400
brush his teeth, and read him a bedtime storybook before he sleeps.

274
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:49,510
I'll pick a storybook for you every day.

275
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:51,740
Yes, Chief.

276
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:53,180
I'm back!

277
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:56,400
Oh, welcome back.

278
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:00,380
Mrs. Yeoju.

279
00:22:00,380 --> 00:22:02,540
Yes? What is it?

280
00:22:02,540 --> 00:22:06,910
I have something to do. Do you mind if I step out for a moment?

281
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:08,340
Where's Chief Jo?

282
00:22:08,340 --> 00:22:11,800
You can go outside! Madam's not going anywhere,

283
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,690
and you should take a break, Mr. Park.

284
00:22:13,690 --> 00:22:17,260
I'll tell Chief Jo.

285
00:22:17,260 --> 00:22:21,620
- Thank you.
- Oh, it's nothing!

286
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:28,720
He seems like such an educated man, very polite.

287
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:33,680
Does he have a wife? Oh, what am I thinking?

288
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,560
How's the dinner preparations coming along?

289
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:37,710
Oh, when I cook the scallops, it's done.

290
00:22:37,710 --> 00:22:42,740
Oh, right. Mr. Park had something to do outside, so I told him he could. It's okay, right?

291
00:22:42,740 --> 00:22:44,360
Yes.

292
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:49,580
Oh, look at me. I forgot to introduce Mr. Park to you, Ms. Park.

293
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:52,400
Well, today's not the only day. You'll see him later.

294
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,800
Right.

295
00:22:57,520 --> 00:23:00,420
Aren't you getting off?

296
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:11,390
Do you think I want to do this?

297
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:15,610
You know it's not okay to stay in that house without permission.

298
00:23:15,610 --> 00:23:18,640
I'll come to get you as soon as I get a house.

299
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:25,920
The realtor said there's a place which seems to meet our conditions, so please wait just until then.

300
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:29,780
Take this fruit basket with you, too!

301
00:23:31,780 --> 00:23:36,300
Tell Hee Sook I'm grateful and sorry. I'll call you later.

302
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:41,400
Why do you want to have a call? Don't even call me!

303
00:24:03,620 --> 00:24:06,060
Dan Dan?

304
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:13,550
Dan Dan? Dan Dan?

305
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:17,240
What's wrong with you?

306
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:19,500
Oh, I'm sorry!

307
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,990
What the heck?

308
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:34,340
Do you think I didn't know that you guys had an affair and chased my birth mom away, and that's why she died?

309
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:37,390
Did you hate my birth mom that much?

310
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:40,750
Why didn't you abandon me, then, if you hated my mom so much?

311
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:43,850
It must have been hard for you to take care of me against your will!

312
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:46,610
Fine! I'll go out now!

313
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:50,080
Fine, get out! Get out! Now!

314
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:55,120
Father! Father, why are you saying that? Don't do that!

315
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:14,780
The customer is unavailable. Please leave a message after the tone.

316
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:19,800
Dan Dan... Where are you?

317
00:25:19,810 --> 00:25:21,700
Are you doing okay?

318
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:31,400
♫ When I walk this road, it makes me cry  ♫

319
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:38,310
♫ It reminds me of that person's touch ♫

320
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:42,380
♫ I couldn't hold her ♫

321
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:47,390
♫ and just trembled my heart ♫

322
00:25:47,390 --> 00:25:51,890
Do all elites raise their kids this way?

323
00:25:51,890 --> 00:25:58,120
Se Jong's only seven, and he's using a room on his own.

324
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:00,480
Won't he be scared of the dark?

325
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:07,310
♫ In case I lose it, I hold it tight ♫

326
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:14,230
♫ But love always runs away, chased by longing ♫

327
00:26:14,230 --> 00:26:17,690
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

328
00:26:17,690 --> 00:26:25,400
[Dad, I've got a job at a good place, and I'm doing well, so don't worry.]

329
00:26:34,170 --> 00:26:37,340
- D-Did they hire a new in-home tutor?
- Yes.

330
00:26:37,340 --> 00:26:43,620
Hey, you barely fired the previous one because she was flirty to Chairman Lee!

331
00:26:43,620 --> 00:26:45,610
Won't this one make you worry again?

332
00:26:45,610 --> 00:26:47,660
It's a countryside girl this time.

333
00:26:47,660 --> 00:26:51,380
She's young and naive.

334
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:52,850
Is that so?

335
00:26:52,850 --> 00:26:54,640
I think we chose well this time.

336
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:58,950
Besides, do you think I'll stand if she flirts with him?

337
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:02,210
It seems like a man should be wealthy and handsome!

338
00:27:02,210 --> 00:27:09,260
Ladies are drooling everywhere, despite that he has three kids.

339
00:27:09,260 --> 00:27:13,100
Oh, it seems like it's going to rain. My back is aching.

340
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:15,890
Ah, my goodness, you brat.

341
00:27:15,890 --> 00:27:18,960
Ah, it hurts!

342
00:27:21,630 --> 00:27:24,140
Oh, well.

343
00:27:43,380 --> 00:27:45,700
What sound is that?

344
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:49,600
Is it a stray cat sound?

345
00:27:55,220 --> 00:27:58,960
What is that sound?

346
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:04,530
Is there a ghost in this house? My goodness!

347
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:40,510
Se Jong!

348
00:28:44,370 --> 00:28:48,940
Se Jong. Why are you crying alone here, at night?

349
00:28:48,940 --> 00:28:53,430
Teacher...

350
00:28:53,430 --> 00:28:56,850
It's okay. It's alright.

351
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:04,970
Se Jong. Did you have a bad dream?

352
00:29:04,970 --> 00:29:07,180
It's alright now.

353
00:29:07,180 --> 00:29:11,350
Teacher's here. You'll be fine.

354
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:16,860
Let's go to your room with me.

355
00:29:16,860 --> 00:29:24,810
No! I don't want to sleep alone in my room tonight.

356
00:29:24,810 --> 00:29:29,110
Alright. Then, should we go to my room?

357
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:31,830
Yes!

358
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:48,330
Teacher. I'm sorry for waking you up and make you tired.

359
00:29:48,330 --> 00:29:49,980
Mr. Se Jong.

360
00:29:49,980 --> 00:29:57,170
You don't have to say sorry to me.

361
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:58,930
Teacher.

362
00:29:58,930 --> 00:30:03,440
Can I ask you a favor?

363
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:06,730
What is it? Tell me.

364
00:30:06,730 --> 00:30:11,390
Would you please keep it a secret that I cried?

365
00:30:11,390 --> 00:30:18,230
If Hyung knows, he'll call me a crybaby and tease me.

366
00:30:18,230 --> 00:30:21,710
I'm not a baby.

367
00:30:21,710 --> 00:30:23,230
Alright.

368
00:30:23,230 --> 00:30:26,900
I won't tell anyone.

369
00:30:26,900 --> 00:30:30,530
- Promise?
- Promise!

370
00:30:36,370 --> 00:30:39,100
I was scared of the thunder.

371
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:42,590
That's why I cried a little bit.

372
00:30:42,590 --> 00:30:47,210
It's not because I missed my mom.

373
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:54,620
I see.

374
00:30:54,620 --> 00:31:03,030
I used to cry a lot because I missed my mom.

375
00:31:03,060 --> 00:31:06,260
Se Jong, you're very brave.

376
00:31:06,260 --> 00:31:09,950
Teacher, you don't have a mom either?

377
00:31:09,950 --> 00:31:13,240
Did she die?

378
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:16,350
Yes.

379
00:31:16,420 --> 00:31:18,320
It's okay!

380
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:25,190
Your mom is in heaven and protecting you.

381
00:32:03,610 --> 00:32:06,340
What's going on?

382
00:32:06,340 --> 00:32:09,360
Where is Se Jong?

383
00:32:13,630 --> 00:32:18,370
Se Chan. Lee Se Chan. Wake up.

384
00:32:18,370 --> 00:32:20,730
What's going on?

385
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:24,500
Where is Se Jong? Did you see Se Jong?

386
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:26,870
Se Jong?

387
00:32:28,580 --> 00:32:32,830
He's not here either. Jenny. Jenny!

388
00:32:32,830 --> 00:32:36,600
Lee Jenny! Lee Jenny! Wake up!

389
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:40,100
You're so annoying. Why don't you even let me sleep?

390
00:32:40,100 --> 00:32:44,590
What are you doing in my room this late? Why the hell are you doing this?

391
00:32:44,590 --> 00:32:51,190
You have no right to barge into my room just because you're my Dad! Get out! Get out!

392
00:32:51,190 --> 00:32:56,650
Jenny, Se Jong is missing. I came in here to look for him. Did you see Se Jong?

393
00:32:56,650 --> 00:32:59,200
Why would you look for Se Jong in here?

394
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,630
Oh, my! What's going on?

395
00:33:01,630 --> 00:33:07,020
Why are you yelling in the middle of the night, Jenny? I'm already trembling because of the thunder and lightning.

396
00:33:07,020 --> 00:33:10,370
Have you seen Se Jong? I can't find Se Jong.

397
00:33:10,370 --> 00:33:13,600
You can't find Se Jong? He's not in his room?

398
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,710
No, I looked everywhere upstairs. I can't find him.

399
00:33:15,710 --> 00:33:19,400
You have to check the first floor too. Are you sure he's not in the kitchen eating something?

400
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:23,060
He's not in the kitchen. I just came from there.

401
00:33:23,060 --> 00:33:29,740
What's going on? Where would that kid go in the middle of the night?

402
00:33:29,740 --> 00:33:32,580
Did he--!

403
00:33:32,580 --> 00:33:35,460
What is it, Madam?

404
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:39,630
What if Se Jong is sleepwalking

405
00:33:39,630 --> 00:33:42,610
and wandering outside in the rain?

406
00:33:42,610 --> 00:33:46,240
Ma'am, how can you say something scary like that?

407
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:49,300
Se Jong has never done that before.

408
00:33:49,300 --> 00:33:51,970
Grandmother, seriously, what's wrong with you?

409
00:33:51,970 --> 00:33:54,530
I'm just worried too.

410
00:33:54,530 --> 00:33:59,570
Can you go to Ms. Park's room, Mrs. Yeoju? That's the only room I didn't check.

411
00:33:59,570 --> 00:34:01,030
Yes, Chairman.

412
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:05,860
That's right. Why isn't Ms. Park here when there is this commotion going on?

413
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:08,510
Hey, let's go.

414
00:34:14,550 --> 00:34:19,710
Oh, thank goodness, he's here. Se Jong is here!

415
00:34:19,710 --> 00:34:22,000
Mrs. Yeoju!

416
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:26,050
Oh, my! Why is Se Jong here?

417
00:34:26,050 --> 00:34:29,610
Ms. Park, what's going on here?

418
00:34:29,610 --> 00:34:32,080
Why is Se Jong here?

419
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:37,610
It's because... Se Jong said he was scared and wanted to sleep here with me.

420
00:34:37,610 --> 00:34:42,400
Then you should have told me or brought him to my room!

421
00:34:45,620 --> 00:34:47,400
Seriously, it's so annoying.

422
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:54,820
What's with all this? I guess I won't be sleeping tonight.

423
00:34:54,820 --> 00:35:00,960
Ms. Park, the whole house was looking for him because he was missing. You didn't know?

424
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:03,530
No. I must have been deep asleep.

425
00:35:03,530 --> 00:35:10,770
Ms. Park! What are you going to do if you sleep so deeply like that when you live in someone else's house?

426
00:35:18,370 --> 00:35:21,580
Honey.

427
00:35:21,580 --> 00:35:24,920
Honey!

428
00:35:29,780 --> 00:35:34,430
Am I dreaming?

429
00:35:34,460 --> 00:35:37,010
Honey.

430
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:39,920
Honey!

431
00:35:43,750 --> 00:35:46,720
What is that?

432
00:35:48,310 --> 00:35:51,860
Honey. Dan Dan's mother!

433
00:35:51,860 --> 00:35:54,550
What the hell happened?

434
00:35:54,550 --> 00:35:59,600
Why are you coming out now? Why?

435
00:35:59,610 --> 00:36:06,210
I've been calling for you all this time!

436
00:36:24,020 --> 00:36:28,970
Hee Sook and her ex-husband reconcile,

437
00:36:28,970 --> 00:36:35,810
and they are living together with their children. How can I stay there?

438
00:36:35,810 --> 00:36:42,360
Then you should have called me. Why did you get soaked in the rain like this and not take a taxi?

439
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:46,290
I did take a taxi here.

440
00:36:46,290 --> 00:36:53,720
But my phone's battery died, so I couldn't see the address you gave me.

441
00:36:53,720 --> 00:36:56,410
We went around the road so many times,

442
00:36:56,410 --> 00:37:03,200
the taxi driver got mad and left, so I ended up like this.

443
00:37:03,220 --> 00:37:06,890
Do you know how scared I was?

444
00:37:06,900 --> 00:37:11,980
The thunder is roaring, and the rain is pouring.

445
00:37:11,980 --> 00:37:18,710
I understand. Drink the honey water. It's hot, so drink slowly.

446
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:24,460
I told you I didn't want to go! I told you!

447
00:37:24,460 --> 00:37:29,860
Okay. It's all my fault. So drink up.

448
00:37:35,020 --> 00:37:37,650
I'm so cold.

449
00:37:40,810 --> 00:37:48,620
You have to eat porridge at least to take medicine. It's not good to take medicine on an empty stomach.

450
00:37:48,620 --> 00:37:52,490
Here. Have a bite, at least.

451
00:37:59,080 --> 00:38:03,040
It's pollack roe and Jangjorim.
 [T/N: Jangjorim is soy sauce braised beef.]

452
00:38:11,290 --> 00:38:16,700
How can the pollack roe be so bouncy, not salty, and has a clean taste?

453
00:38:16,700 --> 00:38:22,890
This isn't the pollack roe we ate. This must be a high-end pollack roe.

454
00:38:26,710 --> 00:38:31,360
The Jangjorim is also so good. It's melting in my mouth.

455
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:34,650
Honey, this must be the best grade Korean beef.

456
00:38:34,650 --> 00:38:40,860
How could they make Jangjorim with such good quality meat?

457
00:38:40,900 --> 00:38:43,850
Eat slowly.

458
00:38:45,470 --> 00:38:50,170
This porridge is so delicious.

459
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:54,590
What porridge taste this sweet?

460
00:38:54,590 --> 00:38:58,470
Are you sure you're really sick?

461
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:04,080
I'm really sick. I have such a high fever.

462
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:07,470
Feel my forehead.

463
00:39:10,330 --> 00:39:12,000
You do have a fever.

464
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:15,010
See? I have a fever.

465
00:39:15,010 --> 00:39:21,530
I'm really sick. Oh, my head...

466
00:39:21,530 --> 00:39:24,620
You'll get better after you eat the porridge and medicine.

467
00:39:24,620 --> 00:39:28,190
For the time being, why don't you stay in a studio until I find a place?

468
00:39:28,190 --> 00:39:31,880
There's a studio available. I'll drop you off later if I can.

469
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:34,360
I don't want to. I want to stay here.

470
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:37,130
Seriously! What if we get caught?

471
00:39:37,130 --> 00:39:39,920
So what if we get caught? All that's going to happen is you get fired.

472
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:46,530
Also, I'm your wife. Is it such a horrible crime to stay here with you?

473
00:39:50,780 --> 00:39:57,190
Okay. I'll bring it up with the Chairman when the situation seems fit since you're only staying for some time.

474
00:39:57,190 --> 00:40:00,450
So be careful until then.

475
00:40:00,450 --> 00:40:06,140
Okay. Of course, I will.

476
00:40:06,140 --> 00:40:12,760
Honey. I suddenly feel much better.

477
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:17,030
But my head still hurts a little.

478
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:26,630
Let Se Jong sleep a little longer.

479
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:27,880
Yes.

480
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:29,770
What about Jenny and Se Chan?

481
00:40:29,770 --> 00:40:33,910
Jenny went to school and Se Chan is still here.

482
00:40:33,910 --> 00:40:38,370
Did Jenny go to school without eating breakfast?

483
00:40:38,370 --> 00:40:40,420
Yes.

484
00:40:54,050 --> 00:40:55,580
Have a good day, Chairman.

485
00:40:55,580 --> 00:40:58,040
- I'm going to school.
- Have a good day at school.

486
00:40:58,040 --> 00:41:01,210
Have a good day.

487
00:41:09,150 --> 00:41:13,820
Ms. Park, let's have a talk.

488
00:41:13,820 --> 00:41:15,990
Yes...

489
00:41:18,820 --> 00:41:22,080
No matter how scared Se Jong was or cried,

490
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:25,620
you shouldn't have brought him to sleep with you in your room.

491
00:41:25,620 --> 00:41:28,200
I was careless.

492
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:32,280
You should have at least contacted me.

493
00:41:32,300 --> 00:41:38,610
From now on, whether it's late-night or not, call me if anything happens with Se Jong.

494
00:41:38,610 --> 00:41:40,420
Yes.

495
00:41:40,420 --> 00:41:42,350
The child was scared and crying in the middle of the night.

496
00:41:42,350 --> 00:41:45,230
She probably couldn't think of calling you.

497
00:41:45,230 --> 00:41:49,350
Ms. Park was also trying to be helpful. That's enough.

498
00:41:52,280 --> 00:42:00,330
Mrs. Yeoju, change all the children's bedsheets to the new ones that I bought today.

499
00:42:00,330 --> 00:42:04,450
Sure!

500
00:42:04,450 --> 00:42:07,460
I think I got on their bad side, Mrs. Yeoju.

501
